fr.gouv.vitam.tools.mailextract.libpst

Class LPStoreExtractor

  • Object
    • fr.gouv.vitam.tools.mailextract.core.StoreExtractor
      • fr.gouv.vitam.tools.mailextract.libpst.LPStoreExtractor

  • public class LPStoreExtractor
extends StoreExtractor
    StoreExtractor sub-class for mail boxes extracted through libpst library.

    The java-libpst is a pure java library for the reading of Outlook PST and OST files.

    This library was originally based off the documentation created through the fantastic reverse engineering effort made by the [libpff](https://sourceforge.net/projects/libpff) project. The library has been improved with information provided by the release of the official PST specs by Microsoft.

    Thanks to Richard Johnson http://github.com/rjohnsondev

        Instantiates a new LP store extractor.
        Parameters:
        protocol - Protocol used for extraction (pstfile)
        server - Server of target account ((hostname|ip)[:port
        user - User account name
        password - Password, can be null if not used
        container - Path to the local extraction target (Thunderbird or Outlook
        folder - Path of the extracted folder in the account mail box, can be null if default root folder
        destRootPath - Root path of the extraction directory
        destName - Name of the extraction directory
        options - Options (flag composition of CONST_)
        logger - Logger used (from Logger)
        Throws:
        ExtractionException - Any unrecoverable extraction exception (access trouble, major format problems...)
